Pr[=b' | Y]`.\n\nBut because of `probOutput_selectElem_eq`, `Pr[=a | X] = Pr[=a' | X]` and similarly for `b`, we get that the products are equal.\n\nBut Lean's instance requires that `X` and `Y` are `sample őĪ` and `sample ő≤`, which are `SPMF`s. \n\nBut perhaps we can use `probOutput_seq_map_prod_mk_eq_mul` for",
